6:
Come on, come on! MOVE, DAMN IT!
Listen to me!
9: You do not have admin privileges.
15:
Even if I manage to stand up, what
then? Not like I can do anything...
18: Am I just gonna give up again?
25:
What, no snappy comeback this
time? Looks like I was right.
33:
That the weak are warped by power.
Seeing you here confirms that it was
the right decision to leave enacting
justice to the machines.
37:
Wait... Did you do all this just to get
rid of me?!
41:
Don't get so full of yourself. What I
find fault with is the imperfect
society that allowed a hero like you
to gain traction.
44:
Although, now that I think about it... I
suppose you are correct, in a sense.
52:
No one can be truly good. That goes
for heroes as much as anybody else.
55:
So in other words, people aren't
suited for heroism. Including me.
58:
As of now, ninety percent of Qualia
City districts have outlawed acts of
hostility between civilians.
62:
Soon there won't be a need for
heroes. After we've finished
removing your body prosthetics, just
go home quietly.
70:
Of all the heroes out there, why are
YOU saying all this?
79:
You're... You're Themis! What about
your master?!
88:
You're supposed to be carrying on
Themis' will! So why are you giving
up?!
93:
Shut it! Don't you dare speak his
name!
103:
Keep my master's name out of your
mouth...
113:
No... No, this isn't right! This isn't
THEMIS!
118: How could you?! HOW COULD YOU?!
121:
There's no way Themis would give
up! It's not RIGHT!
125: Move, you hunk of junk! I. SAID. MOVE!
137:
Heh, I've heard all about you from
Alk. Now... Don't move!
152:
I'll handle the bots here. You two go
on ahead!
159:
Wait, so the troubleshooters are
rioting in the streets?
163:
There's that, and the fact that the
robot task force is too inflexible. They
treat every crime like a major
violation, no matter how small.
166:
By the time I got back, the whole
town was in chaos.
170:
...Hey, sorry if I worried you. I
should've been doing more, instead
of wallowing in my own self-pity.
175:
Themis did a live broadcast stating
the age of heroes is over.
178:
She said the world doesn't need
them anymore. That there will be no
more needless casualties.
182:
I don't think she gets to decide that
though. The future's unpredictable...
And we've all got our own reasons
for wanting to step up.
187: A reason for stepping up, huh?
190:
I couldn't say so before, but I do
have one.
193: I know why I wanted to be a hero.
196:
It's because I wanted to throw
everything away. My terrible
parents, my dead-end life... and
myself.
199:
I thought if I became one of those
sparkling heroes I saw all the time, I
could leave that all behind.
203: That didn't happen though, did it?
207:
It sure didn't. I don't know why I ever
expected it to.
210:
I think I always knew deep down. A
talentless nobody like me isn't suited
to be a hero.
214:
But that doesn't mean I should give
up.
217:
Especially not when that quitter
Themis tells me to!
